Euratom, the European Atomic EnergyCommunity, is issuing a 50 mln Ecu, six-year bond with a couponof 7-1/2 pct and priced at 101-1/2, lead manager BanqueGenerale du Luxembourg SA said.    The bond features a sinking fund from 1989 which willretire 10 mln Ecus worth each year thereafter, giving the issuean average life of four years.    Payment date is April 8 and the issue matures on the samedate in 1993. The bond will be denominated in lots of 1,000Ecus and will be listed in Luxembourg.    Fees total 1-7/8 pct, with 1-1/4 pct for selling and 5/8for management and underwriting, including a praecipuum of 1/8pct. REUTER&#3;